                           <locus target="#75va">Fol. 75va</locus>-vb: Donation note.<q xml:lang="gez">Fol. 75va: ለዝ፡ መጽሐፍ፡ ገድለ፡ አቡነ፡ ዘርእ፡[sic] ቡሩክ፡ ዘወሀቦ፡ ገብረ፡ ትንሣኤ፡ ለታቦተ፡ አቡነ፡ ዘርእ፡[sic] ቡሩክ፡ ንህብ፡ ዘተሣየጦ፡ በንዋዩ፡ ይኩኖ፡ መርሐ፡ ለመንግሥተ፡ ሰማያት። {ዘወሃቦ፡ ለቅዱስ፡ ሚካኤል፡ ነህብ።} ዘሠረቆ፡ ወዘፈሐቆ፡ በሥልጣነ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ፡ ውጉዞ፡ ለይኩን፡ ከመ፡ አርዮስ። {ተፈጸመ፡ በ፲፱፻፳፩፡ ዓመተ።}</q>
                           <q xml:lang="en"/>
                           The note mentions the name of the donor Gäbrä Tǝnśaʾe and the church dedicated to Zärʾa Buruk, under the authority of Mikaʾel Nǝhbi. The name of the latter, and the date of the completion of the writing, 1921 A.M. (= 1928/29 A.D.) seem to have been added later, but possibly in the same hand.
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="e1">- Crude note written in pencil: fol. 75vb: ምህረት፡[sic] ተክለ፡ ማርያም፡ የተወለደ፡ አመት.&#xD;
- Crude note (writing exercise?) written in blue pen: fol. 76v.&#xD;
- Pen trials and writing exercise: fols. 1r, 1v, 2r, 3r, 4r.</item>
                     </list>
